The PDF titled "Assessment of the Tigris River Water Quality in Selected Iraqi Governments" primarily focuses on assessing the water quality of the Tigris River in Iraq. For this assessment, it employs the Weighted Arithmetic Water Quality Index method and the Bhargava method. These methods involve analyzing various water quality parameters. 

From the document, the following parameters relevant to your list have been identified:
- Total Dissolved Solids (TDS)
- pH
- Chloride (Cl-)
- Sulfate (SO4^2-)

Other parameters may also be relevant but are presented in different terms or combined forms in the document. For instance, total hardness could potentially relate to some of the metal ions you listed, but it's not specified individually for each metal. Similarly, parameters like turbidity and electrical conductivity are measured, but they don't directly correspond to the specific substances on your list.

If you agree with this interpretation, I can proceed to the next document and perform a similar analysis.
